#             "definition": "The Bachelor of Science in Biology with a concentration in Biodiversity (BS Biodiversity) is an undergraduate academic degree program that focuses on the study of the variety of life forms found in different ecosystems and their interactions.\n\nBS Biodiversity programs typically cover a wide range of topics related to the study of biological diversity, including taxonomy, ecology, evolution, conservation biology, genetics, and ecosystem management.\n\nStudents in a BS Biodiversity program learn about the patterns and processes that shape biodiversity, including the distribution of species, the factors influencing species richness, and the ecological roles of different organisms in ecosystems. They gain knowledge and skills in areas such as species identification and classification, biodiversity monitoring and assessment, habitat restoration, and conservation strategies.\n\nThroughout the program, students often engage in fieldwork, laboratory experiments, and research projects to gain practical experience with biodiversity assessment techniques and conservation methods. Graduates of BS Biodiversity programs are prepared for careers in various fields related to biodiversity conservation, environmental management, natural resource management, and ecological research. They may work as biodiversity specialists, conservation biologists, wildlife biologists, park rangers, environmental consultants, or research scientists, contributing to the preservation and sustainable management of Earth's biodiversity.",
#             "url": "https://www.msuiit.edu.ph/academics/colleges/csm/programs/biology/bs-biology-general.php"
