#         "BACHELOR OF SCIENCE IN NURSING" : {
#             "definition": "The Bachelor of Science in Nursing (BSN) is an undergraduate academic degree program that prepares students for careers as registered nurses (RNs) in various healthcare settings.\n\nCore Curriculum: BSN programs typically include a core curriculum that covers foundational courses in nursing theory, health assessment, pathophysiology, pharmacology, and nursing ethics. These courses provide students with the fundamental knowledge and skills needed to practice nursing.\n\nClinical Experience: BSN programs incorporate extensive clinical practice experiences where students work directly with patients under the supervision of licensed nurses and clinical instructors. Clinical rotations take place in various healthcare settings, such as hospitals, clinics, long-term care facilities, and community health centers.\n\nSpecialty Areas: BSN programs may offer opportunities for students to explore specialized areas of nursing practice, such as pediatric nursing, maternal-child health, psychiatric-mental health nursing, geriatric nursing, and community health nursing. Students may have the option to choose elective courses or clinical rotations in their areas of interest.\n\nProfessional Development: BSN programs focus on developing students' professional competencies, including critical thinking, communication skills, leadership abilities, and evidence-based practice. Students learn how to collaborate effectively with interdisciplinary healthcare teams and provide high-quality, patient-centered care.\n\nResearch and Evidence-Based Practice: BSN programs emphasize the importance of research and evidence-based practice in nursing. Students learn how to critically appraise research literature, apply research findings to clinical practice, and participate in evidence-based quality improvement initiatives.\n\nPreparation for Licensure: Upon completion of a BSN program, graduates are eligible to take the National Council Licensure Examination for Registered Nurses (NCLEX-RN) to become licensed as registered nurses.",
#             "url" : "https://www.msuiit.edu.ph/academics/colleges/nursing/programs/bs-nursing.php"
