#         "BACHELOR OF PHYSICAL EDUCATION" : {
#             "definition": "The Bachelor of Physical Education (BPEd) is an undergraduate academic degree program designed to prepare individuals for careers in physical education, sports coaching, fitness training, and related fields.\n\nThe BPEd program focuses on providing students with a comprehensive understanding of human movement, exercise science, sports coaching, and physical fitness. Students study various aspects of physical education, including anatomy, physiology, kinesiology, biomechanics, motor development, sports psychology, exercise prescription, and health promotion. The curriculum typically includes theoretical coursework, practical training, and hands-on experience in teaching physical education and coaching sports.\n\nStudents in the BPEd program learn about instructional methods, curriculum design, assessment techniques, and effective communication skills for teaching physical education in schools, colleges, and community settings. They also gain practical experience through internships, practicum placements, and coaching opportunities, where they work with individuals and groups to improve physical fitness, develop sport-specific skills, and promote healthy lifestyles.\n\nGraduates of the BPEd program are prepared to pursue careers as physical education teachers, sports coaches, fitness instructors, athletic trainers, recreation leaders, and health educators. They may work in schools, colleges, universities, sports clubs, community centers, corporate wellness programs, or healthcare facilities, helping individuals of all ages and abilities achieve their fitness and wellness goals. The BPEd program emphasizes the importance of promoting lifelong physical activity, sportsmanship, teamwork, and personal well-being, preparing graduates to make a positive impact on the health and wellness of individuals and communities.",
#             "url": "https://www.msuiit.edu.ph/academics/colleges/ced/programs/pe/Form%205B%20Bachelor%20of%20Physical%20Education.pdf"
