#         "BACHELOR OF SECONDARY EDUCATION (PHYSICS)" : {
#             "definition": "The Bachelor of Secondary Education (BSEd) with a specialization in Physics is an undergraduate academic degree program designed to prepare individuals to become secondary school teachers specializing in teaching physics.\n\nThe BSEd program in Physics focuses on providing students with a solid foundation in physics concepts, theories, and methodologies, as well as the pedagogical skills needed to effectively teach physics to secondary school students. Students enrolled in this program typically undertake a combination of coursework in physics, education, and pedagogy.\n\nThe physics coursework covers fundamental principles in various areas of physics, including classical mechanics, electromagnetism, thermodynamics, quantum mechanics, and modern physics. Students learn about experimental techniques, data analysis, and scientific inquiry methods through laboratory work and theoretical studies.\n\nIn addition to physics content, students also engage in education courses that cover topics such as educational psychology, curriculum development, instructional strategies, classroom management, and assessment techniques. These courses provide students with the knowledge and skills necessary to design and deliver effective physics lessons, cater to diverse learning needs, and create a supportive learning environment.\n\nA significant component of the BSEd program is the teaching practicum, where students gain practical experience by observing and teaching physics lessons in secondary school classrooms under the supervision of experienced mentor teachers and university faculty. This hands-on experience allows students to apply theoretical knowledge in real-world teaching settings, develop their teaching skills, and reflect on their practice.\n\nUpon completion of the program, graduates are eligible to pursue licensure or certification for teaching physics in secondary schools. They are prepared to embark on careers as secondary school physics teachers, where they can inspire and educate students about the fundamental principles of physics, promote scientific inquiry and critical thinking skills, and foster a lifelong love for learning and discovery.",
#             "url": "https://www.msuiit.edu.ph/academics/colleges/ced/programs/sme/FORM%205B%20BSED%20Physics.pdf"
#         },
        
